# ─── Kolekto Admin Panel — Environment Variables ─────────────────────────────
#
# This file is committed to git. It shows required variable names and
# acceptable values, but contains NO real credentials.
#
# HOW TO USE
# ──────────
# 1. Copy this file to `.env.test` and fill in test credentials.
# 2. Copy this file to `.env.production` and fill in production credentials.
# 3. Both target files are gitignored — credentials stay off the repo.
#
# Run modes:
#   npm run dev                     → uses .env (default)
#   npx vite --mode test            → uses .env + .env.test
#   npx vite --mode production      → uses .env + .env.production
#   npm run build                   → uses .env + .env.production (Vite default)
#
# IMPORTANT: Never put the Supabase service_role key here.
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY must be the ANON key only.
# The service_role key bypasses RLS and must never appear in frontend code.

# Backend Express API (kolekto-be-old)
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5050/api

# Supabase project credentials
# Find these at: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=eyJ...anon_key...
